00:52:20.739 --> 00:52:21.820
Give them a sneak peek.

00:52:21.820 --> 00:52:23.000
That's what I'm talking about.

00:52:23.000 --> 00:52:37.920
So they're coming in and the youth groups are coming in and we want to make a massive facility for all these high school kids coming across the street, and they're not going out and sleeping around and doing what they're doing anymore.

00:52:38.399 --> 00:52:41.359
But you give into stuff like that.

00:52:41.359 --> 00:52:44.549
That's what I'm trying to tell you.

00:52:44.549 --> 00:52:57.690
So when you've given to me, and this is where I sow my money, this is why I'm trying to help.

00:53:00.453 --> 00:53:01.627
And I told Diana, I said, "This is my heart: a harvest.

00:53:01.627 --> 00:53:06.760
" But people want to know 30, 60, 100-fold return when you call for the angels to help you.

00:53:17.260 --> 00:53:17.570
You can't draw from a well that is dry.

00:53:17.570 --> 00:53:18.809
It's by multiplication.

00:53:18.809 --> 00:53:23.330
But you've got to look at your heavenly account.

00:53:23.330 --> 00:53:25.290
Keep track of your seeds.

00:53:25.290 --> 00:53:32.069
Keep track of how much you've given to the church.

00:53:33.726 --> 00:53:35.040
And you say, "Well, I just pluck it.

00:53:37.893 --> 00:53:38.195
" I don't just dump it and pluck it.

00:53:52.400 --> 00:53:52.880
You know, like, "Well, you just let it hit the bucket—change.

00:54:12.857 --> 00:54:13.234
" I am strategic in everything I do when God tells me to do something and I say I'm going to write it down.

00:54:13.234 --> 00:54:16.770
So this is what's in my heavenly account.

00:54:16.770 --> 00:54:22.789
So I have a legal right in the spirit realm to call that forth.

00:54:22.789 --> 00:54:32.319
You cannot call forth $100,000 if you don't have a hundred thousand multiplied seed in there.

00:54:32.319 --> 00:54:33.280
It's spiritual law.

00:54:33.280 --> 00:54:39.040
But people want to get all flaky and they go, "Well, it's over here.

00:54:57.839 --> 00:54:58.047
I believe in God for $10 million, brother.

00:54:58.671 --> 00:55:02.512
" And I'm like, "But do you have $10 million of the seed in the ground?

00:55:02.512 --> 00:55:13.035
Because if you don't, you might as well say Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star because you aren't going to receive it.

00:55:13.035 --> 00:55:17.339
I don't care what you're saying.

00:55:26.280 --> 00:55:26.560
The seed always multiplies.

00:55:26.560 --> 00:55:31.773
A seed always produces after its own kind, but it always comes back in multiplication.

00:55:31.773 --> 00:55:49.440
If a farmer planted one row of corn and said, "I'm believing for this whole field to come in, brother," and we're out there going, "Oh," and you're out there praying over the seed, but you only planted one row, but I believe for the whole field, you're crazy.

00:55:49.440 --> 00:55:51.419
It's not going to happen.

00:55:51.419 --> 00:55:53.409
I don't care how much you pray.

00:55:53.409 --> 00:55:58.630
If the seed isn't in the ground, you're not going to reap it.

00:56:00.924 --> 00:56:15.867
And you can only call by spiritual law and asking the angels and the Lord to help you by what you have sown into the local church, to your ministry where you are.

00:56:15.867 --> 00:56:17.235
Help your pastor.

00:56:17.235 --> 00:56:18.017
Help your congregation.

00:56:18.017 --> 00:56:19.679
Where do you go to church?

00:56:19.679 --> 00:56:26.871
And if you say, "Well, I don't want to give there," then why are you going to church there?

00:56:26.871 --> 00:56:27.884
That's dumb.

00:56:27.884 --> 00:56:30.969
Go to a place where you get fed.

00:56:45.749 --> 00:56:48.919
And when you get fed by the Word of God there, help that ministry out.

00:56:48.919 --> 00:56:52.200
Even if it's just $10, help them.

00:56:52.200 --> 00:57:02.319
If you sit in their pew and go to the bathroom and flush their toilet or whatever, use their toilet paper and use their soap on your hands.

00:57:02.319 --> 00:57:04.850
Use your faith to believe God with them.

00:57:04.850 --> 00:57:05.689
There's Pastor Chip right here.

00:57:09.085 --> 00:57:09.416
You want to show him, Pastor Chip?

00:57:09.416 --> 00:57:12.480
He's the one in the black hat.

00:57:24.696 --> 00:57:24.912
He goes down there and ministers to these kids and he's eating a snow cone.

00:57:24.912 --> 00:57:26.208
Show them the Red Zone.

00:57:26.208 --> 00:57:32.619
That's where my heart's at: the youth of this nation.

00:57:32.619 --> 00:57:41.902
The Lord told me, "Satan came after the youth hard and I'm coming after them harder.

00:57:42.684 --> 00:57:49.267
" And we're going to bring in the greatest harvest of souls this world has ever seen before.

00:57:49.267 --> 00:57:54.346
And it's all going to start in a place like Collinsville, Oklahoma.

00:57:57.010 --> 00:58:00.911
It's going to start in places like this that are small, that are just across the street from a stadium.

00:58:16.926 --> 00:58:17.189
And you can see the flag in the background.

00:58:17.189 --> 00:58:18.240
That's the stadium.

00:58:18.240 --> 00:58:20.640
That's how close the Red Zone is.

00:58:20.640 --> 00:58:30.1000
We put the cones out there so that the kids are safe, but the stadium's right across the street.

00:58:30.1000 --> 00:58:35.360
They come across the street.

00:58:56.160 --> 00:58:56.460
That's how close it is.

00:59:10.850 --> 00:59:11.160
So just believe in God.

00:59:11.160 --> 00:59:23.262
I'm trying to show you things to get excited, but I want you to be motivated in your ministries, what God has called you to do in your area.

00:59:30.880 --> 00:59:31.520
It's all hands on deck right now.

00:59:32.799 --> 00:59:40.610
And if you're not doing something to bring in the harvest, if you're not doing something in your local community, why aren't you?

00:59:40.610 --> 00:59:49.920
If you live in a small town or a big city, help your church; help them bring in the harvest.

00:59:59.671 --> 00:59:59.813
I talked to a mega-minister today and we were talking.

00:59:59.813 --> 01:00:03.492
I said, "The Lord told me," and he said, "Brandon, what are we looking for?

01:00:03.492 --> 01:00:07.380
" I said, "This is what I'm believing for.

01:00:07.380 --> 01:00:10.448
" He said, "I'm not—you're not waiting on me.

01:00:21.173 --> 01:00:23.900
I'm waiting on you.

01:00:31.291 --> 01:00:36.480
You bring in my harvest, I'll come and get you.

01:00:36.480 --> 01:00:39.400
" Jesus said that to me, 'Brandon, I'm waiting on the fruit.

01:00:40.210 --> 01:00:43.313
I have long patience for the fruit, but time is running out.

01:00:43.313 --> 01:00:49.080
What are you going to do to help me bring in this harvest?

01:00:58.926 --> 01:00:59.234
For the harvest is plentiful and the laborers are few.

01:00:59.234 --> 01:01:02.640
' There are billions dying and going to hell.

01:01:02.640 --> 01:01:04.754
What will you do?

01:01:04.754 --> 01:01:15.136
Are we just going to sit back and pray and have these little prayer services and just sit there and go, 'Well, Jesus, get them all saved'?

01:01:15.136 --> 01:01:16.623
He is waiting on us.

01:01:16.623 --> 01:01:20.400
Get a fire shut up in your bones.

01:01:23.573 --> 01:01:26.976
And no, that's why I said, 'Lord, I'm tired of hearing about Smith Wigglesworth.

01:01:26.976 --> 01:01:29.965
I'm tired of hearing about Kathryn Kuhlman.

01:01:29.965 --> 01:01:40.471
I'm tired of hearing about Rachel Teafatiller and all these prayer generals and the people of the past.

01:01:40.471 --> 01:01:43.099
I don't want to hear about it anymore.

01:01:43.099 --> 01:01:45.050
What about my generation?

01:01:45.050 --> 01:01:48.457
What about the people behind this camera right now?

01:01:48.457 --> 01:01:49.599
What about your church?

01:01:49.599 --> 01:01:52.354
What about the churches in Chicago?

01:01:52.354 --> 01:02:02.030
What about the churches in Philadelphia, New York City, Miami, and Atlanta, and all these other places that need a touch from Jesus and they're desperate?

01:02:02.030 --> 01:02:12.309
' I know God stationed me in a little place to go to church over here and visit.

01:02:14.690 --> 01:02:17.278
And he said, 'Go back there and help them.

01:02:33.248 --> 01:02:33.392
Pray for them.

01:02:33.392 --> 01:02:39.466
' And I saw the youth coming in by the hundreds—not thousands because there are not thousands there—by the hundreds.

01:02:45.359 --> 01:02:46.560
But it takes one person; one person led Billy Graham to Jesus, and Billy Graham led millions.

01:02:54.080 --> 01:03:01.057
Who was the person that led my friends to Jesus?

01:03:01.057 --> 01:03:06.000
I must mess up his name again: Maldonado.

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:09.017
Maldonado has led millions to Jesus.

01:03:10.319 --> 01:03:11.119
He talks about him.

01:03:11.119 --> 01:03:14.987
Maldonado is going to Brazil in a couple weeks.

01:03:16.423 --> 01:03:16.880
And who led him to Jesus?

01:03:27.280 --> 01:03:27.900
But it took one spark to spread a major fire.

01:03:27.900 --> 01:03:30.826
It takes one person to reach millions.

01:03:42.160 --> 01:03:42.606
And he says, 'I have somebody here.

01:03:42.606 --> 01:03:47.119
' So whatever your vision is, do it with all your heart.

01:03:47.119 --> 01:03:48.270
Don't do it halfway.

01:03:48.270 --> 01:04:02.989
It's like I told Pastor Chip, I said, 'We've got to make the greatest facility with what God has given us so that everybody in Oklahoma, Tulsa, and all these areas talk about how great the Collinsville, Oklahoma youth group is.

01:04:02.989 --> 01:04:11.599
' They are in a place with a population of hardly anybody; it has probably two stoplights.

01:04:11.599 --> 01:04:17.013
But why not do it and do it well?

01:04:17.013 --> 01:04:26.689
Why should we get the hand-me-downs in church and people go, 'Well, you know, it's just the youth'?

01:04:26.689 --> 01:04:28.910
No, it's the next generation.

01:04:28.910 --> 01:04:31.236
It's the next generation.

01:04:41.947 --> 01:04:45.240
For you were once a youth and so was I.

01:04:45.240 --> 01:05:09.219
So, that's why I try to tell you all a little bit more about me, but I don't know if you even wanted to hear that tonight, but people want to know about this kind of stuff I'm talking about.

01:05:09.219 --> 01:05:12.000
And I say it by the unction of the Holy Spirit.

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:19.520
Be bold about what God's called you to do in these last days, but do it with all your heart.

01:05:19.520 --> 01:05:24.924
Get a backbone like a crowbar, get enthusiastic about it, and get some passion.

01:05:24.924 --> 01:05:28.020
Don't say, 'Well, it's just somebody else's responsibility.

01:05:28.020 --> 01:05:33.679
' When Jesus told me, he said, 'It's all hands on deck.

01:05:33.679 --> 01:05:38.149
Brandon, will you help me bring in the harvest?

01:05:38.149 --> 01:05:42.504
' I saw his hands, and Jesus was in the field.

01:05:42.504 --> 01:05:50.811
He was in overalls and he had a piece of wheat in his mouth and he put it up here.

01:05:50.811 --> 01:06:00.903
I saw the wheat bowing down and I saw harvest equipment, and the barn was full of the glory and the anointing.

01:06:07.579 --> 01:06:07.829
And he said, 'Do you see the angel armies that are coming?

01:06:07.829 --> 01:06:12.759
I've released the host of heaven to help you, for you're not alone.

01:06:12.759 --> 01:06:16.040
For there are more with you than there are with them.

01:06:16.040 --> 01:06:21.869
' You're not doing this alone, ladies and gentlemen, for there's more with you than there are with them.

01:06:23.459 --> 01:06:29.253
And I saw the angels and the host of heaven coming out, and they looked like a waterfall coming on this earth.

01:06:30.009 --> 01:06:33.029
And there were two angels per one unsaved person, and they were lined up.

01:06:42.480 --> 01:06:42.880
And he said, 'I'm giving you a window of uninterrupted and unhindered.

01:06:46.902 --> 01:06:53.511
For Satan has blinded the eyes of the unbeliever, and I'm calling in the unsaved, for I've come to save that which was lost.

01:06:53.511 --> 01:06:57.016
' The harvest equipment is the anointing.

01:06:59.079 --> 01:07:05.164
And I saw Jesus walking amongst the wheat, and he was rubbing his hands all in it.

01:07:05.911 --> 01:07:11.460
And as I could see his hands rubbing through that wheat, he had massive holes in his hands, massive holes.

01:07:19.360 --> 01:07:19.599
And I could see through his hands.

01:07:22.559 --> 01:07:22.769
And I could see the wheat through his hands.

01:07:23.820 --> 01:07:25.875
And he said, 'Brandon, I suffered for every single one of them.

01:07:25.875 --> 01:07:28.640
I suffered for every single one of them.

01:07:28.640 --> 01:07:31.239
Help me bring in the harvest.

01:07:31.239 --> 01:07:33.620
Help me bring in the harvest.

01:07:33.960 --> 01:07:35.954
The harvest is plentiful and the laborers are few.

01:07:35.954 --> 01:07:38.907
Help me bring in the harvest.

01:07:38.907 --> 01:07:42.613
' I looked at him and I said, 'I'll do my best.

01:07:42.613 --> 01:07:55.143
As for me and my house, Lord, we will serve you.

01:07:59.800 --> 01:07:59.1000
We will do whatever it takes to help bring in the harvest.

01:07:59.1000 --> 01:08:03.199
' He said, 'I know you will.

01:08:13.640 --> 01:08:13.840
I know you will.

01:08:13.840 --> 01:08:20.436
' I'm just trying to tell you tonight there's so many things we can get stuck on.

01:08:20.436 --> 01:08:43.782
There's so many problems we have in our lives—the storms of life, the cares of this world that choke out everything and keep us distracted from what this person's saying or that person, and people persecute you for the word's sake.

01:08:43.782 --> 01:08:46.696
But it doesn't matter.

01:08:46.696 --> 01:08:56.560
All I know is when I stand before my Father, he'll judge me by what I've done for him and he'll look at me and say, 'Well done, thy good and faithful servant.

01:08:56.560 --> 01:08:59.016
' Or, 'Well, you could have done better.

01:08:59.016 --> 01:09:05.172
' But I don't want to stand before him and say, 'Hey, at least I tried.

01:09:05.172 --> 01:09:06.026
' I tried.

01:09:06.026 --> 01:09:10.503
I gave it all I got.

01:09:10.503 --> 01:09:13.880
I gave it all I got.

01:09:23.387 --> 01:09:23.760
And I want you to say that for your community.

01:09:23.760 --> 01:09:25.866
Help your pastors; help them.

01:09:34.460 --> 01:09:34.800
Don't sit idly by and say, 'Well, it's on them.

01:09:34.800 --> 01:09:38.280
' You know, 'I work, whatever.

01:09:38.280 --> 01:09:43.269
I don't really have time to volunteer my time.

01:09:43.269 --> 01:09:45.226
' You know what?

01:09:45.226 --> 01:09:48.400
Everybody has the same hours a day.

01:09:48.400 --> 01:09:49.999
Everybody goes to work.

01:09:49.999 --> 01:09:55.486
Everybody busts their hiney to make ends meet for their home.

01:09:55.486 --> 01:09:58.720
But you can be a parking lot attendant.

01:10:01.140 --> 01:10:02.126
You can work being an usher at the door.

01:10:02.126 --> 01:10:05.386
There's something you can do to help your pastor.

01:10:05.386 --> 01:10:12.426
There's something you can do to help your local church and say, 'Hey, I'm going to pour myself out right here.

01:10:12.426 --> 01:10:16.827
' And it may just be picking up trash in the parking lot.

01:10:31.246 --> 01:10:31.543
And you say, 'Well, that's nothing.

01:10:31.543 --> 01:10:41.310
' But it's significant to the visitor that just showed up and said, 'You know what?

01:10:41.310 --> 01:10:43.740
They don't care about nothing.

01:10:43.740 --> 01:10:48.822
There's trash, there's cigarette butts, there's all kinds of stuff going on out here.

01:10:48.822 --> 01:10:50.479
This place is dirty.

01:10:50.479 --> 01:10:55.600
I don't ever want to come back here again.

01:10:55.600 --> 01:11:12.700
' The impression that you leave for the first impression when you walk in there could be what makes or breaks that person to give Jesus Christ a chance in their heart and say, 'Hey, I want to make him my Lord.

01:11:12.700 --> 01:11:14.400
' There's excellence in it.

01:11:14.400 --> 01:11:16.479
God's a God of excellence.

01:11:16.479 --> 01:11:24.373
That's why he talks to me all the time about my weight: 'Brandon, I want you to be healthy.

01:11:24.373 --> 01:11:27.440
I don't want you to be obese.

01:11:30.026 --> 01:11:33.440
You display me on that camera to millions of people; I want you to take care of yourself.

01:11:33.440 --> 01:11:42.559
' And it isn't easy for Brandon.

01:11:42.559 --> 01:11:55.920
Today I had a smoothie and a wrap, but my flesh—whenever my daughter said, 'Daddy, I want an ice cream,' I said, 'Okay, honey.

01:11:55.920 --> 01:12:03.100
' But I'm learning to say it's good for you, but it's not good for me right now.

01:12:17.349 --> 01:12:17.634
I have to work out that stuff for Brandon Biggs.

01:12:17.634 --> 01:12:21.211
I'm just trying to be real with you all.

01:12:21.211 --> 01:12:27.440
But stretch your faith to believe God for more than just your needs.

01:12:27.440 --> 01:12:46.503
If you're just believing for your electric bill and your water and your gas and your house to be paid off or your car or whatever, believe God for your local church, that they're able to do outreaches like this, and pray for your people.

01:12:46.503 --> 01:12:48.651
Does it show the stadium?

01:13:08.640 --> 01:13:08.930
I get excited when I see the stadium.

01:13:11.417 --> 01:13:11.874
I love football.

01:13:11.874 --> 01:13:27.270
Football is my favorite time of year.

01:13:38.200 --> 01:13:38.660
I don't know about you, but I love football.

01:13:38.660 --> 01:13:41.086
Did you show it?

01:13:41.086 --> 01:13:46.160
Show just a little bit of that.

01:14:04.650 --> 01:14:04.820
Is that the church, right?

01:14:04.820 --> 01:14:05.840
Just play some of it.

01:14:05.840 --> 01:14:09.245
Just play fast clips like that.

01:14:29.120 --> 01:14:39.675
They're all showing up and they're all coming there.

01:14:39.675 --> 01:14:57.229
I'm just trying to say: come up with an idea for your local community.

01:16:27.813 --> 01:16:28.307
This is our idea.

01:16:28.307 --> 01:16:45.653
For those that have blessed our ministry, you've given into this and you don't even know it.

01:16:50.381 --> 01:17:22.229
I want to say thank you.

01:17:22.239 --> 01:17:32.719
There's a lot of kids that are getting saved and delivered there, and it's a blessing.

01:18:03.119 --> 01:18:03.679
I don't talk about stuff like that, but I'm just being real and transparent.

01:18:08.813 --> 01:18:38.080
The people who have blessed my ministry have given to this—a lot of it—and I've tried to really support this church and help them because they have a vision.

01:18:38.080 --> 01:18:40.680
So it's exciting.

01:18:40.680 --> 01:20:26.091
But the whole point of what I want to tell you all is this: you can't draw from a well that is dry.

01:20:26.091 --> 01:20:36.470
So, bless your local church.

01:20:36.480 --> 01:20:43.360
Help them.

01:20:43.360 --> 01:21:07.111
And the angels—you send them out and they'll bless you.

01:21:07.111 --> 01:21:08.142
You know that.

01:21:08.142 --> 01:21:22.303
Tonight, if you're here and you've never asked Jesus Christ to be your Lord and personal Savior, and you tell me, 'Brandon, I'm not saved.

01:21:22.303 --> 01:21:38.387
I'm just watching you and I wanted to know what was being said in the news, but I'm feeling a tug on my heart tonight.

01:21:38.387 --> 01:21:57.072
' You say, 'Brandon, I want to give my heart to Jesus Christ.

01:21:57.072 --> 01:22:18.470
I'm tired of running.

01:22:18.480 --> 01:23:17.943
' You may be at the end of your rope.

01:23:17.943 --> 01:23:39.430
You may be here tonight and you say, 'Brandon, I feel like self-harm.

01:24:09.748 --> 01:24:10.262
I feel like all these things.

01:24:12.664 --> 01:24:13.008
I feel so heavy.

01:24:13.008 --> 01:24:15.072
I've battled depression and anxiety.

01:24:15.072 --> 01:24:34.750
I've had the worst week from heck I could ever tell you about.

01:24:41.474 --> 01:24:41.862
I lost my job.

01:24:41.862 --> 01:25:39.977
' There are so many people that have so much going on.

01:25:43.744 --> 01:25:51.568
I got diagnosed with an incurable disease and I'm so broken.

01:25:51.568 --> 01:26:07.680
I just need somebody to pray for me.

01:26:07.680 --> 01:26:12.288
But tonight's the night you give Jesus Christ your heart.

01:26:12.288 --> 01:26:40.173
If you've never asked Jesus Christ to be your Lord and personal Savior, I want to give you the invitation and tell you there's a heaven to gain and a hell to shun.

01:26:41.173 --> 01:26:49.949
The very shoes you put on today to go to work, the undertaker might be taking them off tonight.

01:26:49.949 --> 01:26:53.300
No one's promised tomorrow, ladies and gentlemen.

01:26:53.300 --> 01:27:07.480
When we see the days approaching and there's so much darkness and so much going on right now, it's shocking when we watch the news.

01:27:19.760 --> 01:27:39.439
But you're going to have to be in the right place at the right time in the days ahead, because if you're not listening to the voice of the Lord, there's a great opportunity you could go home early.

01:27:39.439 --> 01:27:45.157
'You're trying to scare me, Brandon.

01:27:45.157 --> 01:27:48.187
' No, I'm trying to prepare you.

01:27:58.400 --> 01:27:58.640
You better be all-in with Jesus.

01:27:58.640 --> 01:28:02.080
If you're riding the fence and you're in sin right now, you better run from it.

01:28:02.080 --> 01:28:04.150
It's time to be all-in with Jesus.

01:28:08.880 --> 01:28:09.050
Say, 'Jesus, I give You my all.

01:28:09.050 --> 01:28:10.069
I'm not playing church anymore.

01:28:10.069 --> 01:28:11.259
